U.S. Forest Service - Sequoia National Forest
September 9 at 1:30 PM ¬∑

Forest Service Temporarily Closes All National Forests in California- Due to unprecedented and historic fire conditions throughout the state, the USDA Forest Service Pacific Southwest Region is announcing a temporary closure of an additional ten National Forests, meaning all eighteen National Forests in California are now closed.

The closure of the additional ten forests will be effective at 5:00 pm today. These additional forests include the Eldorado National Forest, Klamath National Forest, Lassen National Forest, Mendocino National Forest, Modoc National Forest, Six Rivers National Forest, Plumas National Forest, Shasta-Trinity National Forest, Tahoe National Forest, and Lake Tahoe Basin Management Unit. This decision will be re-evaluated daily as conditions change.

For news release, please visit: https://fs.usda.gov/detail/r5/news-events/?cid=FSEPRD801394

Granite Hills High Law, Justice, and Ethics (LJE) Pathway student Maria Basurto Pelcastre has been selected by NAF for a student internship through its headquarters in New York City. She is one of only six students in the nation to earn the internship.

Basurto Pelcastre will begin the virtual 84-hour paid internship on September 10.

Since 1980, NAF has been partnering with high-need communities to improve outcomes for students by implementing NAF academies ‚Äì small learning communities within existing high schools.

NAF has grown from one NAF Academy of Finance in New York City to hundreds of academies across the country focusing on growing industries including: finance, hospitality & tourism, information technology, engineering, and health sciences. During the 2019-2020 school year, over 110,000 students attended 620 NAF academies across 34 states, plus DC, Puerto Rico, and the US Virgin Islands. In 2019, NAF academies reported 99% of seniors graduated with 86% of graduates planning to go to college.

Can you find good character through distance learning? Does it exist in the virtual world? Absolutely!

The Tulare County Office of Education is delighted to accept nominations for the 25th Annual Kids of Character Awards beginning today! What started as a celebration of students modeling the Six Pillars of Character in 1996, has turned into a national character recognition model which has honored tens of thousands of Tulare County students!

Educators, parents, and community members are encouraged to take a few moments to nominate Tulare County students (grades TK-12) who are exhibiting great character during these challenging times. Do you see great character online or around the house? Are your students doing something extraordinary to help the community? Nominate them today!

The nomination period is open through September 24. Nominated Tulare County students will be recognized during National CHARACTER COUNTS! Week, October 19-24.

Visit www.tcoe.org/KidsOfCharacter today.

Did You Know?

ParentSquare has many different Features that each receive a unique type of Notification. ParentSquare allows users to select their preferred delivery method for Post notifications. When a message is posted, users have the option to receive an email, text, app notification or a combination of methods. Users can also decide if they want an Instant email or a Digest email that is delivered at 6:00 pm with all posts from that day.

If you have several students and would like to use the Digest setting, simply click on your name at the upper right corner of the ParentSquare page. You can make changes in the Notification Settings section.

If you need to update your email or phone, please contact the school to have that information updated.

post_text:
PUSD uses ParentSquare as its communication platform. You can download the app through the Apple Store or Google Play Store depending on your device.

ParentSquare makes it easy to register for ParentSquare from the app. Follow the steps below:

1) Open up the ParentSquare App. Enter your email or cell phone number. The email and/or cell phone number should match what is in your school's information system or database.

Note: If your email or phone number is not recognized by ParentSquare, you can 'Request Access' or call your school office and ask them to update your contact information.

2) Next, create your password and confirm your password. Click Continue.

3) You will receive a registration code via email or text. Enter your registration code and click 'Verify'. This will take you to your ParentSquare home feed!

Note: If your registration link has expired, a new one will need to be sent to you. Please contact your school's admin and ask for a new link to be sent to you.

Our Enrollment Center is now open from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m., Monday through Friday. If your student has never attended a PUSD school, you can go to portervilleschools.com, and go to the Student Enrollment page under the Parents menu. Our Aeries Internet Registration site allows you to quickly start the process of registering a student for enrollment in Porterville Unified School District.

Upon completion of the online registration forms you will need to print the forms and bring the printed forms and the documents listed below, in person, to the PUSD Enrollment Center located at 600 W. Grand Ave.

If you are unable to complete the forms, we have computers available in the Center for you. For more information, please call (559) 793-2487.

Parents, staff, and community members are encouraged to attend our Parent Forum as we discuss our plan for reopening schools for the 2020-2021 school year. The forum will take place on Monday, July 27, in a virtual setting through Zoom. The English version will be from 4 p.m. to 5 p.m. and the Spanish version from 5:30 p.m. to 6:30 p.m.

We will discuss the changes in distance learning for the start of the year, compared to last spring based on new COVID-19 guidelines.

The forum also will include information on the new CDE (California Department of Education) requirement, the Learning Continuity and Attendance Plan that all districts must adopt by September 30.

shared_text:
Tulare County Office of Education
July 14 at 3:04 PM ¬∑

It's a good night to dust off that telescope! You can catch Jupiter at its brightest tonight in the southern sky as the gas giant reaches ‚Äúopposition." Opposition occurs when a superior planet (Mars, Jupiter, Saturn, Uranus, Neptune) and the Sun are on opposite sides of the Earth, forming a strait line. Jupiter can be spotted with the naked eye in the southern sky all night in the constellation Sagittarius.

Need help finding it? Download our free, handy Astronomy Wheel to help navigate the night sky at bit.ly/3gz0EQK. For an added bonus, use a telescope to see Jupiter's banding, great red spot, and its four Galilean moons.

Follow us to receive regular astronomy updates from TCOE's Planetarium & Science Center.

Tulare County Fire Department
June 23 at 5:41 PM ¬∑

As the 4th of July approaches celebrating with Fireworks are not allowed in some areas of Tulare County. How do you know if you live in an area where Safe & Sane Fireworks are legal?

Safe & Sane fireworks are only allowed in the Local Response Area‚Äôs (LRA) of Tulare County. Areas of Tulare County that are located within the State Responsibility Area (SRA) NO FIREWORKS are allowed.

How do you know if you live in an area where fireworks are allowed?

You can go to CALFire web site below to see if your address is located within the SRA or LRA of Tulare County.

https://www.arcgis.com/home/webmap/viewer.html?useExisting=1&layers=5ac1dae3cb2544629a845d9a19e83991

Please remember to be safe when using Safe & Sane fireworks this 4th of July. Any firework that does not have the State of California Fire Marshall Safe & Sane logo on the package is illegal within California.

If your student has never attended a PUSD school, our Aeries Internet Registration site allows you to quickly start the process of registering a student for enrollment in Porterville Unified School District.

Upon completion of the online registration forms you will need to print the forms and bring the printed forms and the documents listed below, in person, to the PUSD Enrollment Center located at 600 W. Grand Ave.

For more information, please call (559) 793-2487.

https://www.portervilleschools.org/apps/pages/index.jsp?uREC_ID=212973&type=d&pREC_ID=859523

US National Weather Service Hanford California
June 1 at 1:52 PM ¬∑

A warming trend will bring temperatures to well above normal again throughout the central California interior by the middle of the week as high pressure builds back into the area. Triple digit heat will be widespread in the San Joaquin Valley Wednesday and Thursday while temperatures in the hottest locations of the lower Sierra foothills and the Kern County deserts will be above the century mark. Thankfully, the hot weather will be short lived. Temperatures will begin to cool down on Friday, and the cooling trend will continue through the weekend.

Tulare County Office of Education
May 27 at 3:41 PM ¬∑

Don't miss next week's Theatre Company Masterclass featuring Jordan Litz! Jordan is a graduate of Fresno Pacific University who is now living and working in New York City. Since moving to New York City, he has played Warner in "Legally Blonde" at the Argyle Theater, sung in the "Radio City Christmas Spectacular featuring the Rockettes,‚Äù and is now the understudy for Fiyero in the national tour of "Wicked.‚Äù

Open to students of all ages - including college students - the Masterclass Series features ongoing Zoom-based presentations allowing students to speak with TCOE Theatre Company alumni, staff, and guest speakers to see how they utilize their collegiate training, how they prepare for auditions, and what it‚Äôs like to work professionally on famous stages.

To register for the workshop featuring Jordan Litz, being held Wednesday, June 3, at 1:00 p.m., visit www.tcoe.org/TheatreMasterClass.

Open to students of all ages - including college students - the Masterclass Series features ongoing Zoom-based presentations allowing students to speak with TCOE Theatre Company alumni, staff, and guest speakers to see how they utilize their collegiate training, how they prepare for auditions, and what it‚Äôs like to work professionally on famous stages.

To register for the workshop featuring Jordan Litz, being held Wednesday, June 3, at 1:00 p.m., visit www.tcoe.org/TheatreMasterClass.

What are ‚ÄòP-EBT‚Äô or Pandemic EBT benefits?

Due to coronavirus (COVID 19), children who are eligible for free or reduced-price meals at school will get extra food benefits. These food benefits are called Pandemic EBT or P-EBT benefits. P-EBT benefits help families in California buy food when school is closed.

Who is eligible for P-EBT benefits?

Children are eligible for P-EBT benefits if:

Their school is closed due to coronavirus (COVID 19); and
They are eligible for free or reduced-price school meals

https://ca.p-ebt.org/en/

Tulare County Office of Education
May 21 at 3:34 PM ¬∑

May is Mental Health Awareness Month. In these uncertain times, setting up a bedtime routine which promotes quality sleep is very important to our overall mental health! When we are tired, it‚Äôs harder to regulate our emotions and cope with challenging situations. This is especially true for children who may already struggle to express their feelings. Creating a bedtime routine which promotes relaxation may include a mindfulness practice, a warm bath, a bedtime story and cuddles, and/or sipping a warm beverage. It is also important to end screen time at least 1-2 hours before bed.

For more resources from TCOE's Behavioral Health Services, visit https://www.tulareselpa.org/copy-of-aap

On Friday, May 22, Porterville Unified School District will distribute free Kinsa thermometers to families at Sequoia Middle School, Strathmore High School, and Butterfield Charter School.

On Tuesday, May 26, thermometers will be available at West Putnam Elementary School, Roche Avenue Elementary School, and Vandalia Elementary School. Monache High School will have a distribution on Monday, June 1, while Bartlett Middle School will have one on Tuesday, June 2.

All distributions will take place from 9 a.m. to 10 a.m.

Each family will receive one thermometer and can utilize the Kinsa Health app, which will send information to public health professionals and licensed clinicians to get personalized care recommendations every time someone logs a symptom, diagnosis or feverish temperature.

The app can be downloaded through the Apple Store or Google Play Store. Please download the app before you arrive to pick up your thermometer.

For more information on Kinsa Health, please go to https://www.kinsahealth.co/.

WWW2.CALSTATE.EDU
CSU Chancellor Timothy P. White Statement on Fall 2020 University Operational Plans | CSU

California State University
May 12 at 3:10 PM ¬∑

The CSU announces plans to conduct a majority of classes virtually at all 23 campuses for the fall 2020 term, with limited exceptions. Campuses will remain open and ready to serve students.

‚ÄúThis approach to virtual planning is necessary for many reasons," said CSU Chancellor Timothy White. "First and foremost is the health, safety and welfare of our students, faculty and staff, and the evolving data surrounding the progression of COVID-19‚Äìcurrent and as forecast throughout the 2020-21 academic year. This planning approach is necessary because a course that might begin in a face-to-face modality would likely have to be switched to a virtual format during the term if a serious second wave of the pandemic occurs, as forecast. Virtual planning is necessary because it might not be possible for some students, faculty and staff to safely travel to campus. Said another way, this virtual planning approach preserves as many options for as many students as possible."

Read Chancellor White's full statement for more information.

Starting on Monday, April 27, Porterville Unified School District will be switching its Meals at No Cost service to a once-a-week delivery on Mondays from 11 a.m. to 12:30 p.m. Sites will continue to have Drive Thru and Walk Up options. All meals will come complete with five breakfast and five lunch entrees, fruits and vegetables, and low-fat milks. Meals are distributed for off-site heating and consumption.

Service will take place only at the following sites: Roche Avenue Elementary, Butterfield Charter School, Bartlett Middle, Pioneer Middle, Granite Hills High, Monache High, Porterville High, and Strathmore High, as well as the current rural routes (1, 2, 3, 6, 7).

For more information on the Meals at No Cost service and rural routes, go to portervilleschools.org. #porterville #portervilleunified

Parents, staff, and community members are encouraged to participate in our final LCAP informational meeting and be a part of Porterville Unified School District planning to learn about the Local Control Funding Formula (LCFF) system. The meeting is Wednesday, April 22, from 4 p.m. to 5:15 p.m.

Please note that this meeting will take place virtually through a Zoom conference call due to COVID-19 restrictions. If you wish to participate, please contact your school site administrator for more information.

We will be reviewing the feedback from the last LCAP meeting on School Climate, the recommendations from previous LCAP meetings, and get your final vote on your top 3 priorities for focus goals. Thank you for your support and patience.

We will be reviewing the feedback from the last LCAP meeting on School Climate, the recommendations from previous LCAP meetings, and get your final vote on your top 3 priorities for focus goals. Thank you for your support and patience.

Porterville Unified School District is proud to announce the addition of another route for our Meals at No Cost Service, beginning next Monday, April 6.

Route No. 7 will start at the northwest corner of Prospect and Crystal near the Family Health Care Network building from 11 a.m. to 11:20 a.m.

The second stop will be from 11:30 a.m. to 11:50 a.m. at Poplar Ave. and South Chase Terrace, just west of the Shell gas station.

The final stop will be from 12 noon to 12:30 p.m. on the corner of Jaye Street and Springville Avenue in front of the Villa Robles Apartments.

Each child must be present in order to pick up a ‚ÄúGrab-N-Go‚Äù lunch and breakfast meal to eat at home. Children need to eat their Lunch meal or refrigerate them within 30 minutes of pickup. This includes refrigerating breakfast meals for the following day.

post_text:
Dear Porterville Unified School District Parents, Guardians, and Family Members:

We are constantly evaluating our Meals at No Cost Service program in order to create the most efficient manner in delivering these meals to the community.

Beginning on Monday, April 6, we will be consolidating the following sites:

Harmony Magnet Academy will be moved to Strathmore High

Pioneer Middle School will be moved to Vandalia Elementary

Belleview Elementary will be moved to Bartlett Middle

Sequoia Middle will be moved to Westfield Elementary

Citrus High will be moved to Los Robles Elementary

Thank you for your patience. We will keep you updated on any further changes.
